### Test Pharmacy Payments Endpoint

# Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### 0. Check if there are existing orders for pharmacy 23
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/pharmacy/23

### 1. Create a pharmacy order
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": 1,
  "pharmacyId": 23,
  "medicineId": 1,
  "quantity": 2,
  "totalAmount": 150.00,
  "status": "pending",
  "OrderId": "ORD-TEST-001"
}

### 2. Create a payment for the order
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/initialize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+254700000000",
  "amount": 150.00,
  "type": "order",
  "orderId": 1,
  "returnUrl": "http://localhost:3000/payment-verify"
}

### 3. Test the pharmacy payments endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/payments/pharmacy/23
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}} 